WEBVTT

00:08:27.357 --> 00:08:31.358
I figured I'd go out on a limb
and just make a wish list

00:08:31.382 --> 00:08:34.595
of the teenager's dream library.

00:08:35.698 --> 00:08:39.890
Over 200 brand-new books
were sent to my room piece by piece.

00:08:40.672 --> 00:08:45.245
Every day there were new deliveries
and my kids would exclaim with glee,

00:08:45.269 --> 00:08:47.226
"This feels like Christmas!"

00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:48.330
(Laughter)

00:08:48.354 --> 00:08:49.519
Then they'd say,

00:08:49.543 --> 00:08:52.415
"Ms. Sumner, where did
these books come from?"

00:08:52.439 --> 00:08:53.655
And then I'd reply,

00:08:53.679 --> 00:08:57.655
"Strangers from all over the country
wanted you to have these."

00:08:58.274 --> 00:09:00.951
And then they'd say, almost suspiciously,